        "The organization's impact is driven by a highly efficient cost structure, achieving an estimated <cite id=\"13\">cost of $3.29 per beneficiary</cite>. This efficiency is supported by a <cite id=\"14\">program expense ratio of 81.3%</cite> as reported in their 2022 Form 990, though Charity Navigator credits them with an <cite id=\"15\">81.3% ratio</cite> when accounting for their specific '100% model' structure. Their governance is equally strong, featuring a <cite id=\"16\">91% independent board</cite> and comprehensive policies including a <cite id=\"17\">conflict of interest policy</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "founded in 2006, charity: water is a non-profit organization dedicated to <cite id=\"1\">bringing clean and safe drinking water</cite> to people in need globally. The organization is distinguished by its unique funding model and high operational transparency, having <cite id=\"2\">funded 9,395 water projects</cite> according to its most recent filings. In 2022, the charity reported <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $96,818,300</cite>, maintaining a robust financial position to support its mission across <cite id=\"4\">Asia and Africa</cite>. The organization focuses on sustainable, community-led solutions including <cite id=\"5\">piped systems, BioSand filters, and drilled wells</cite> to ensure long-term water security. By partnering with local organizations, they implement infrastructure that is maintained by the communities themselves, which is a core pillar of their <cite id=\"6\">direct provision delivery model</cite>. Their commitment to transparency is reflected in their <cite id=\"7\">perfect 100.0/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, a rating that encompasses accountability, culture, and leadership. Furthermore, the charity holds a <cite id=\"8\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level of recognition for non-profit disclosure. While the organization is widely known for its '100% model'\u2014where private donors cover operating costs so public donations go directly to water projects\u2014it remains a <cite id=\"9\">SADAQAH-ELIGIBLE</cite> entity, making it a strong choice for Muslim donors looking to support high-impact humanitarian work in the extreme poverty sector.",
